cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CV 

This paper deals with cross-lingual understanding (XLU) and document classification, which are both sub-fields of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as unsupervised pre-training and unsupervised data augmentation, which fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with information retrieval (IR) as it involves classifying documents, which is a task in IR. Finally, the paper may also fall under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it uses visualizations to analyze the results.
